[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":599},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide\u002F":575,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide\u002F":584},"\u002Fother\u002F20201020\u002F1425713503\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":557,"date":558,"description":559,"extension":560,"lang":561,"meta":562,"navigation":563,"path":564,"readingMinutes":565,"seo":566,"standalone":567,"stem":568,"tags":569,"tldr":572,"updated":572,"url":573,"__hash__":574},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide.md","CodePen Quick Start (10-Minute Tour)","5135034125",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":541},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,37,41,44,67,73,76,82,85,88,94,97,105,111,116,119,125,128,134,137,140,146,149,155,158,164,173,176,182,185,188,194,198,201,207,210,216,219,225,231,238,241,261,264,270,274,277,283,286,292,296,307,313,319,327,333,348,354,357,360,366,369,376,382,386,395,400,403,409,412,418,421,427,430,433,438,441,447,450,454,457,462,465,471,475,486,489,495,498,504,509,514,520,526,529,533],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"If you're a frontend dev and need to quickly share a small demo, CodePen is a fantastic WYSIWYG online HTML\u002FCSS\u002FJS editor. Lots of people use it for sharing effects and practice — but plenty haven't gotten comfortable with it. So this post is a CodePen intro.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"codepen","CodePen",[17,25,26],{},"Pen as in \"writing pad\". If you're frontend or you ever need to whip up a quick web interaction, CodePen is what you reach for. Tons of devs share visual effects and experiments there:",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"Lots of practice","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.06.01.png",[17,35,36],{},"If you're stuck for inspiration, CodePen's a great place to browse.",[12,38,40],{"id":39},"main-features","Main features",[17,42,43],{},"CodePen has three core types of objects:",[45,46,47,55,61],"ul",{},[48,49,50,54],"li",{},[51,52,53],"strong",{},"Pen"," (snippet)",[48,56,57,60],{},[51,58,59],{},"Project"," (multi-file workspace)",[48,62,63,66],{},[51,64,65],{},"Collection"," (group of Pens)",[17,68,69,70,72],{},"Most of the time, ",[51,71,53],{}," is enough for frontend dev work. Project and Collection are used less. This post focuses on Pen.",[17,74,75],{},"Annotated menu screenshot:",[17,77,78],{},[30,79],{"alt":80,"src":81},"Menu","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FaFX0Ahk.png",[12,83,53],{"id":84},"pen",[17,86,87],{},"The Pen interface:",[17,89,90],{},[30,91],{"alt":92,"src":93},"Pen UI","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FFHRYBPx.png",[17,95,96],{},"Left side — HTML, CSS, JS editors. Right side — live preview.",[17,98,99,100,104],{},"CodePen supports Emmet. Type something like ",[101,102,103],"code",{},".w100"," then hit Tab and it expands. CodePen also previews the expansion as you type:",[17,106,107],{},[30,108],{"alt":109,"src":110},"Emmet preview","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGO05GAG.png",[17,112,113],{},[30,114],{"alt":109,"src":115},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FY2VpR1K.png",[17,117,118],{},"Not happy with the layout? Click \"Change View\" at the top to switch direction:",[17,120,121],{},[30,122],{"alt":123,"src":124},"Change View","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FNtMO9Aq.png",[17,126,127],{},"You can also change the display mode when someone opens the Pen — annotated below:",[17,129,130],{},[30,131],{"alt":132,"src":133},"Display modes","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2022.17.45.png",[17,135,136],{},"(Heads up — display mode requires the Pen to be saved first. Otherwise only Change View works.)",[17,138,139],{},"To load CDN libraries (jQuery, Bootstrap, etc.), click \"Settings\" at the top or the gear icon below:",[17,141,142],{},[30,143],{"alt":144,"src":145},"Settings","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FZecxihC.png",[17,147,148],{},"Then add the CDN URLs in the appropriate section:",[17,150,151],{},[30,152],{"alt":153,"src":154},"CDN","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FOz17ITy.png",[17,156,157],{},"If you want a CSS Reset, CodePen has one built in:",[17,159,160],{},[30,161],{"alt":162,"src":163},"Reset CSS","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FO4rieNb.png",[17,165,166,167,172],{},"(If you don't know the difference between Reset CSS and Normalize.css, see ",[168,169,171],"a",{"href":170},"\u002Fcss\u002F20210807\u002F3641451940\u002F","Reset CSS vs Normalize.css (article in Mandarin)",".)",[17,174,175],{},"You can also search for CDN libraries by name from within Settings:",[17,177,178],{},[30,179],{"alt":180,"src":181},"Bootstrap search","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQDTZJMY.png",[17,183,184],{},"Load order matters — for example, Bootstrap recommends loading jQuery before Bootstrap's JS.",[17,186,187],{},"Final shot — annotated full UI:",[17,189,190],{},[30,191],{"alt":192,"src":193},"UI annotations","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FJtPlGlV.png",[12,195,197],{"id":196},"preprocessors","Preprocessors",[17,199,200],{},"For more advanced devs — you can write Pug instead of HTML, or Sass\u002FSCSS instead of plain CSS. In Settings, find \"HTML Preprocessor\" and pick \"Pug\":",[17,202,203],{},[30,204],{"alt":205,"src":206},"HTML Preprocessor","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.33.14.png",[17,208,209],{},"After switching, the pane label changes to \"HTML (Pug)\":",[17,211,212],{},[30,213],{"alt":214,"src":215},"Pug pane","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FDuBuZEH.png",[17,217,218],{},"To view the compiled HTML, click the arrow next to the pane label and pick \"View Compiled HTML\":",[17,220,221],{},[30,222],{"alt":223,"src":224},"View Compiled HTML","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.38.06.png",[17,226,227],{},[30,228],{"alt":229,"src":230},"Compiled output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F3w8r72Q.png",[17,232,233,234,237],{},"Heads up — while in \"Compiled\" view, the HTML pane is ",[51,235,236],{},"read-only",". Switch back via \"View Uncompiled Pug\".",[17,239,240],{},"The dropdown options translated for reference:",[45,242,243,246,249,252,255,258],{},[48,244,245],{},"Format HTML — auto-format the HTML",[48,247,248],{},"Analyze HTML — run analysis",[48,250,251],{},"Maximize HTML Editor — make the HTML pane large",[48,253,254],{},"Minimize HTML Editor — minimize the HTML pane",[48,256,257],{},"Fold All — collapse HTML",[48,259,260],{},"Unfold All — expand HTML",[17,262,263],{},"The same flow works for CSS — switch to Less \u002F Sass \u002F SCSS:",[17,265,266],{},[30,267],{"alt":268,"src":269},"CSS Preprocessor","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.40.42.png",[12,271,273],{"id":272},"auto-format","Auto-format",[17,275,276],{},"CodePen supports format — select all → Shift+Tab, or click the format button:",[17,278,279],{},[30,280],{"alt":281,"src":282},"Format button","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FU83MGUl.png",[17,284,285],{},"After clicking, CodePen reformats:",[17,287,288],{},[30,289],{"alt":290,"src":291},"Formatted","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.44.50.png",[12,293,295],{"id":294},"pen-gotcha","Pen gotcha",[17,297,298,299,302,303,306],{},"The most common mistake people make in CodePen — don't put ",[101,300,301],{},"\u003Cbody>"," or ",[101,304,305],{},"\u003Chead>"," tags in the HTML pane. It can cause unexpected breakage, usually because the CDN-loaded styles get double-loaded. The output might \"kind of\" look right but you shouldn't do it:",[17,308,309],{},[30,310],{"alt":311,"src":312},"Wrong","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FvMRVayc.png",[17,314,315],{},[30,316],{"alt":317,"src":318},"Right","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fgo3T4NS.png",[17,320,321,322,302,324,326],{},"Why? CodePen wraps the HTML pane inside an iframe with its own shell. If you also add ",[101,323,301],{},[101,325,305],{}," inside the pane, you get nested duplicate structure:",[17,328,329],{},[30,330],{"alt":331,"src":332},"Broken structure","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.53.53.png",[17,334,335,336,339,340,344,345,347],{},"You can see ",[101,337,338],{},"\u003Cmeta>"," ending up ",[341,342,343],"em",{},"inside"," ",[101,346,301],{}," — weird.",[17,349,350],{},[30,351],{"alt":352,"src":353},"Correct structure","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.54.36.png",[17,355,356],{},"So don't paste a full HTML document into the HTML pane. Layout breakage, JS-not-running — these are usually caused by this pattern. The most common one is duplicate CSS CDN loading making it impossible to debug.",[17,358,359],{},"CodePen actually warns you if you do this — click into the warning:",[17,361,362],{},[30,363],{"alt":364,"src":365},"Warning","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLAGO4rJ.png",[17,367,368],{},"The message:",[17,370,371,372,375],{},"\"Just HTML that goes in the ",[101,373,374],{},"body"," goes here. Learn more\"",[17,377,378,379,381],{},"Basically — keep only what goes inside ",[101,380,301],{}," in the pane, not outside it.",[12,383,385],{"id":384},"explore-topics","Explore Topics",[17,387,388,389,394],{},"CodePen has framework-specific templates too — Vue, React, etc. Hit ",[168,390,385],{"href":391,"rel":392},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Ftopics\u002F",[393],"nofollow",":",[17,396,397],{},[30,398],{"alt":385,"src":399},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2021.58.35.png",[17,401,402],{},"For Vue specifically, you'll see lots of templates:",[17,404,405],{},[30,406],{"alt":407,"src":408},"Vue templates","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2022.00.01.png",[17,410,411],{},"For a clean Vue environment, click \"Open Vue Editor\":",[17,413,414],{},[30,415],{"alt":416,"src":417},"Open Vue Editor","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2022.00.59.png",[17,419,420],{},"Now you're in a Vue dev environment:",[17,422,423],{},[30,424],{"alt":425,"src":426},"Vue editor","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVoTRpAM.png",[12,428,59],{"id":429},"project",[17,431,432],{},"Quick word on Project. Think of Project as a real multi-file workspace — you get a file tree, real folder structure:",[17,434,435],{},[30,436],{"alt":59,"src":437},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-10-20%2022.03.56.png",[17,439,440],{},"Free accounts get one Project:",[17,442,443],{},[30,444],{"alt":445,"src":446},"One Project","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FOlusQHe.png",[17,448,449],{},"So in practice you don't see Project used much — you have to delete the existing one to create another. Unless you pay.",[12,451,453],{"id":452},"customizing-codepens-editor","Customizing CodePen's editor",[17,455,456],{},"To customize the editor — click your avatar → Settings:",[17,458,459],{},[30,460],{"alt":144,"src":461},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQjKUZcb.png",[17,463,464],{},"Switch to \"Editor Preferences\" — you can tweak editor styling here:",[17,466,467],{},[30,468],{"alt":469,"src":470},"Editor Preferences","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F4k3HtKl.png",[12,472,474],{"id":473},"emmet-customization","Emmet customization",[17,476,477,478,481,482,485],{},"In VSCode you sometimes customize Emmet — e.g., ",[101,479,480],{},"aqq"," expands to ",[101,483,484],{},"a.qq",". Here's how to do the same on CodePen.",[17,487,488],{},"In \"Editor Preferences\", scroll to the bottom — \"Emmet Custom Snippets\":",[17,490,491],{},[30,492],{"alt":493,"src":494},"Emmet Custom Snippets","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FIwAdZtY.png",[17,496,497],{},"Fill in the fields:",[17,499,500],{},[30,501],{"alt":502,"src":503},"Customize Emmet","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FN3x3KTc.png",[17,505,506,507,394],{},"Test in the editor — type ",[101,508,480],{},[17,510,511],{},[30,512],{"alt":480,"src":513},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fl6sZcHA.png",[17,515,516,517,394],{},"Tab → expands to ",[101,518,519],{},"\u003Ca href=\" \" class=\"qq\">\u003C\u002Fa>",[17,521,522],{},[30,523],{"alt":524,"src":525},"Custom Emmet result","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FrSqmn48.png",[17,527,528],{},"CodePen has plenty more — this is just the most-useful slice.",[12,530,532],{"id":531},"references","References",[45,534,535],{},[48,536,537],{},[168,538,23],{"href":539,"rel":540},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io",[393],{"title":542,"searchDepth":543,"depth":543,"links":544},"",2,[545,546,547,548,549,550,551,552,553,554,555,556],{"id":14,"depth":543,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":543,"text":23},{"id":39,"depth":543,"text":40},{"id":84,"depth":543,"text":53},{"id":196,"depth":543,"text":197},{"id":272,"depth":543,"text":273},{"id":294,"depth":543,"text":295},{"id":384,"depth":543,"text":385},{"id":429,"depth":543,"text":59},{"id":452,"depth":543,"text":453},{"id":473,"depth":543,"text":474},{"id":531,"depth":543,"text":532},"Misc","2020-10-20 20:56:29","CodePen is a great spot for frontend devs to put together quick demos — WYSIWYG online HTML\u002FCSS\u002FJS editor. This post is a quick intro for anyone who hasn't used it much — Pens vs. Projects vs. Collections, working with the editor, adding CDNs, preprocessors (Pug, Sass\u002FSCSS\u002FLess), formatting, Emmet customization, and the things that commonly trip people up (don't put `\u003Cbody>` or `\u003Chead>` tags in your HTML pane).","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide","4",{"title":6,"description":559},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide",[23,570,571],"CodePen Tutorial","CodePen Basics",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fcodepen-quick-start-guide\u002F","XMUvDQuC98ZB6Rx8dd2YZ4mV4_-s-GOsADFfpfWyKPE",{"newer":576,"older":580},{"url":577,"title":578,"date":579},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F21\u002Fpixijs-v5-37-stats-js\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (37) - Adding stats.js to Watch Your FPS","2020-10-21 15:25:20",{"url":581,"title":582,"date":583},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2020\u002F10\u002F14\u002Flearn-hexo-31-common-issues\u002F","(31) Learning Hexo from Scratch - Extras: Common Questions","2020-10-14 00:00:01",[585,590,595],{"url":586,"title":587,"date":588,"readingMinutes":589},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":591,"title":592,"date":593,"readingMinutes":594},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":596,"title":597,"date":598,"readingMinutes":565},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00",1784020368942]